  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA309-kiḷavi">itu varaivu nīṭa vāṟṟāḷeṉak kavaṉṟu tāṉāṟṟāḷākiya tōḻiyait talaimaka ḷāṟṟuvittatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is how SHE gave strength to the confidante who herself did not have the strength to bear it, being anxious that she would not bear it when the marriage was delayed.</p>
        </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA309">
<l>            nekiḻnta tōḷum vāṭiya variyun</l>
<l>            taḷirvaṉap piḻantaveṉ ṉiṟaṉu nōkki</l>
<l>            yāṉcey taṉṟiva ṭuyareṉa vaṉpi</l>
<l>            ṉāḻal vāḻi tōḻi vāḻaik</l>
<l>            koḻumaṭa lakalilait taḷitalaik kalāvum 5</l>
<l>            perumalai nāṭaṉ kēṇmai namakkē</l>
<l>            viḻuma māka laṟiyuna rilleṉak</l>
<l>            kūṟuvai maṉṉō nīyē</l>
<l>            tēṟuvaṉ maṉyā ṉavaruṭai naṭpē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>Don’t be overcome by love, oh friend,</l>
<l rend="indent">looking at [my] emaciated shoulders and [my] faded lines</l>
<l rend="indent3">and my colour that lost the beauty of sprouts,</l>
<l rend="indent">saying</l>
<l rend="indent3">“her misery has been made by me”.</l>
<l>You, won’t you say, for sure,</l>
<l rend="indent">that he is not one who knows<note place="foot">Understood like this, we have to take <term xml:lang="ta">aṟiyunar</term> as a singular honorific, referring to HIM, inspite of <term xml:lang="ta">nāṭaṉ</term>, which is singular. We might also consider a general statement: "there is nobody who knows that it is misery..."  Or perhaps, as a way of dealing with the better-attested variant: "today they are knowing that it is distress..."</note> that it is becoming misery to us<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">namakkē</term>: is -<term xml:lang="ta">ē</term> here simply used to fill up the metrical foot?</note>,</l>
<l rend="indent2">the intimacy with the man from a land of great mountains,</l>
<l rend="indent3">where the dripping tips of the leaves widening rich fronds</l>
<l rend="indent3">of the plantain are perturbed?</l>
<l>I do believe in the friendship he has.</l>
      </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
